com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin

Class SequenceAnnotationGenerator.SelectionRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.plugin.SequenceAnnotationGenerator.SelectionRange
  • Enclosing class:
    SequenceAnnotationGenerator

    public static class SequenceAnnotationGenerator.SelectionRange
extends Object
    represents a rectangular selection range in a list of sequences, and also behaves like a Linked List in that it provides a link to the next SelectionRange in a chain of selections (see getNext().

      • SequenceAnnotationGenerator.SelectionRange

        public SequenceAnnotationGenerator.SelectionRange(int firstSelectedSequence,
                                          int lastSelectedSequence,
                                          int firstSelectedResidue,
                                          int lastSelectedResidue,
                                          SequenceAnnotationGenerator.SelectionRange next)
        Parameters:
        firstSelectedSequence - between 0 and the number of sequences -1
        lastSelectedSequence - between 0 and the number of sequences -1. This must not be less than firstSelectedSequence.
        firstSelectedResidue - between 0 and the maximum length of sequences -1
        lastSelectedResidue - between 0 and the maximum length of sequences -1. This must not be less than firstSelectedResidue.
        next - Refers to another selection range for situations where multiple ranges are selected (e.g. when the user ctrl-drag-selects multiple regions in the sequence viewer). May be null to indicate there are no more selection ranges.
